1
00:00:01,340 --> 00:00:03,110
(Episode 119)

2
00:00:03,110 --> 00:00:04,410
Right here.

3
00:00:05,180 --> 00:00:08,650
I have concrete proof.
As stipulated in the contract,

4
00:00:08,980 --> 00:00:11,650
you can either pay
the triple penalty and cancel,

5
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:15,690
or I can have all your assets seized,
as per the notarized document.

6
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:17,090
Choose.

7
00:00:19,290 --> 00:00:22,760
- That's impossible.
- "Impossible" is not an option. What now?

8
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:25,660
Call Chairman Ma right now.

9
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:29,600
If you can't pay the penalty fee,
I'm seizing all of your shares.

10
00:00:32,740 --> 00:00:33,940
The penalty fee...

11
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:36,440
I'll pay it.

12
00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:38,710
Now.

13
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,210
Manager Lee.

14
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:44,620
Withdraw the funds
from my Swiss account...

15
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:48,990
and transfer them to the escrow account
provided by Chairman Ali.

16
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:54,260
Wire the 30 million dollars now.

17
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:02,300
Chae Hwa Young,
are you really crying over this?

18
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:05,300
I lost my daughter.

19
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:09,510
And you're crying just because
you lost some money?

20
00:01:09,610 --> 00:01:11,040
You wretched woman.

21
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,950
From now on,
I'll make you shed tears of blood.

22
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:25,290
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

23
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,460
Mom, you worked so hard.

24
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:35,570
It's all thanks to you and Baek Ho.

25
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:37,800
You were truly incredible.

26
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:41,270
I'm relieved we were able to hurt
Chae Hwa Young even just a little.

27
00:01:41,470 --> 00:01:44,180
Though we still have a long way to go
to make her cry tears of blood.

28
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:46,850
I had no idea
you were such a good actress.

29
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:50,010
Tae Pyung, you weren't there
to see her performance in person.

30
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,580
It was unbelievable. I'm telling you...

31
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:53,790
it was an award-worthy performance
for Best Actress.

32
00:01:53,850 --> 00:01:56,320
Come on, are you teasing me?

33
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:58,660
So what happened with the money?

34
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:01,690
After Chairman Ali confirms it,
Tommy is going to send it over.

35
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:03,190
It was company money to begin with,

36
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:04,700
so we need to put it back
where it belongs.

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,670
Speak of the devil.

38
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:09,930
Go on answer it.

39
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:16,070
Hi, Chairman Ali. This is Jang Mi.

40
00:02:16,410 --> 00:02:20,310
I heard you transferred the money
from Chae Hwa Young to my account.

41
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:23,550
- So is Chae Hwa Young broke now?
- I'm not sure.

42
00:02:23,620 --> 00:02:26,280
We don't know the exact size
of her slush fund.

43
00:02:26,350 --> 00:02:27,550
Thank you very much.

44
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:31,420
Next time you visit Korea,
it will be my pleasure to host you.

45
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,190
Please take care, sir.

46
00:02:33,490 --> 00:02:35,860
Okay, thank you. Bye.

47
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,800
(Deposit: 40 million dollars)

48
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:42,070
The 40 million dollars came in.

49
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:45,240
So we've managed to intercept
Chae Hwa Young's 30 million.

50
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,170
For someone like Chae Hwa Young
who values money more than life,

51
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:50,810
this is her just deserts, right?

52
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,310
Yes. You did great, ma'am.

53
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:55,750
Mom, Jang Mi, and Baek Ho.

54
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,080
You all worked really hard.

55
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:03,620
By the way,
how do you actually know Chairman Ali?

56
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:05,290
Jang Mi is surprisingly well-connected.

57
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:07,130
I told you before.

58
00:03:07,130 --> 00:03:09,290
Back when I was working part-time
at a concert hall,

59
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:12,700
I happened to help Chairman Ali
when he was in a tight spot.

60
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,700
We've kept in touch ever since,

61
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,270
and it looks like our paths
were meant to cross again.

62
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,770
What is all this?
It's all just worthless paper.

63
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:23,580
I'm ruined. I'm completely ruined.

64
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:27,380
This is no time to fall apart.
You need to pull yourself together.

65
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:30,520
How am I supposed to pull myself together
after losing 30 million dollars?

66
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:35,250
I scraped that money together
using every trick in the book.

67
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:37,190
All that money
I fought tooth and nail for...

68
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:41,030
How could I lose it all so easily?

69
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:45,800
What's going on, ma'am?

70
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:47,930
What do you mean it all fell through
and you paid a penalty?

71
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:50,370
Jun Ho.

72
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,710
I just can't believe this.

73
00:03:57,580 --> 00:04:00,240
Don't tell me it was canceled
because of the affair.

74
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:03,510
- Did the entire contract get canceled?
- Stop it.

75
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:05,480
I don't need you piling on.

76
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:07,550
I already feel like dying...

77
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:09,790
after having to cough up
30 million dollars for the penalty.

78
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,990
What kind of life have you led?

79
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:15,460
How have you lived your life
that you keep getting in my way...

80
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,660
- at every crucial moment?
- Kang Jun Ho.

81
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:20,330
Are you finished?

82
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,470
Do you have any idea
who I've suffered hellish humiliation...

83
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:26,070
and lived like a monster for?
It was all for you.

84
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:29,310
I was going to put you
on the throne at Dream...

85
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:31,110
so you wouldn't have to bow to anyone.

86
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:33,510
That's why I got blood on my hands.

87
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:35,810
Don't make excuses.

88
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:38,250
You stole one of the twins
and disregarded human life...

89
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,920
long before you ever met me.

90
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:41,720
It wasn't for me.

91
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:44,120
It was for your endless greed.

92
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:46,560
All the filthy messes you've made...

93
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:49,960
will end up dragging me down
into the filth and getting me killed.

94
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:51,330
Got it?

95
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,300
You're going too far.

96
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:58,170
She tries so hard to protect you.

97
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:01,810
- How can a son say such terrible things?
- Manager Lee, stay out of this.

98
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:02,910
You're just as bad.

99
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:07,050
Clinging to CEO Chae like a parasite
doing all her dirty work...

100
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,710
You're her accomplice
who ruined everything.

101
00:05:09,780 --> 00:05:11,050
That's right.

102
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,250
Just like you said,
I'm filthy and despicable.

103
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:15,050
But what now?

104
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:18,320
All the money I made that way
has already been taken from me.

105
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:22,090
Is this the time for idle chatter?

106
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:26,860
We should be figuring out
how to get that hard-earned money back.

107
00:05:30,030 --> 00:05:31,570
It's over with Hills Hotel.

108
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:35,810
The deposit, our credibility,
and the rest of the funds are all gone.

109
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:36,940
How do you expect to get any of it back?

110
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:40,040
And it's only a matter of time
before the Chairman finds out...

111
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:42,350
the fact that we've been
hiding this slush fund.

112
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:46,320
We'll be lucky if we don't get
kicked out of Dream Hotel.

113
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:47,520
Understand?

114
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,150
Jun Ho.

115
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:51,220
Kang Jun Ho.

116
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:56,060
I'm going crazy.
I'm going to kill Han Young Ja.

117
00:05:57,060 --> 00:05:58,930
I won't let her get away with this.

118
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,170
I won't let her get away with this.
I'll get my money back.

119
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,150
Open the door!

120
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:15,810
Han Young Ja!

121
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:21,550
Let go of me. What has gotten into you?

122
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,090
My gosh!

123
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,490
Are you satisfied now?

124
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:34,270
How did you know I would be?

125
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:42,410
How dare you lay a hand on me?
If you hit me once, I'll hit you twice.

126
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:45,940
You evil witch.
How dare you ruin my plans?

127
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,550
Who do you think you are
barging into my office...

128
00:06:47,550 --> 00:06:48,910
and passing out those photos?

129
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:51,680
Do you have any idea
how much I've lost because of you?

130
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,580
I lost all my money.

131
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,090
Give my money back!

132
00:06:55,150 --> 00:06:56,450
How dare you!

133
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:04,400
You lost your money?
That's the best news I've heard all day.

134
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:07,470
Congratulations on losing your money.

135
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:11,640
Now can you stop screaming
and talk nicely?

136
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,970
You just barged into someone else's house.

137
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:15,010
What is this uncivilized behavior?

138
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:18,740
Why don't you show this side of yourself
to Kang Nam Bong?

139
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:21,250
Shut up.

140
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:23,880
Han Young Ja, I'm ruined because of you.

141
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:26,050
It's all your fault.

142
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:29,090
That's all it takes to ruin you?

143
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:32,690
Chae Hwa Young,
you're not so tough after all.

144
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:36,430
I might even be richer than you now.

145
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:39,530
Han Young Ja, I'm going to kill you.

146
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:42,670
I'm going to tear you to shreds.

147
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:47,140
- Do it. Go on do it.
- You witch! Die!

148
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:48,940
- Ma'am, please calm down.
- Let go.

149
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:50,910
You can't act like this here.

150
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:54,110
What is going on here?

151
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:55,350
Han Young Ja.

152
00:07:55,550 --> 00:07:57,380
What on earth did you do to Hwa Young?

153
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:00,450
Kang Nam Bong. You stay out of this.

154
00:08:01,090 --> 00:08:04,360
You moved out.
What are you even doing here?

155
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:07,090
I brought the divorce papers.
I need you to sign them.

156
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,030
Hwa Young, what happened?

157
00:08:09,090 --> 00:08:13,060
Han Young Ja showed our photos
to Chairman Ali,

158
00:08:13,130 --> 00:08:15,300
and I lost 30 million dollars.

159
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:18,340
Can you blame me for losing my mind?

160
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:20,040
You showed the photos of me and Hwa Young?

161
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:23,640
- Are you out of your mind?
- It's true you were having an affair.

162
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:26,440
What's wrong with sharing her the truth?

163
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,280
Look at her.
Listen to the way she's talking.

164
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:34,250
I lost everything because of Han Young Ja.

165
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,250
You're crying over a measly
30 million dollars?

166
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,820
For the sin of making others
cry tears of blood,

167
00:08:38,890 --> 00:08:41,660
- don't you think you got off cheap?
- Han Young Ja, that's enough.

168
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:44,060
I'm not finished yet.

169
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:46,800
Chae Hwa Young,
if you have any energy left to fight,

170
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,000
save it.

171
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:51,100
I'm just getting started.

172
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,470
What?

173
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:57,840
Now to our perfect victory...

174
00:08:57,980 --> 00:09:00,010
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

175
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:08,950
While pretending to be Chairman Ali,

176
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:11,390
and Chae Hwa Young was kneeling
and begging at my feet,

177
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:14,290
I thought my heart was going to leap
out of my chest.

178
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,960
In my entire life,
I have never felt so satisfied.

179
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,700
It was a first for me.

180
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:22,630
That's what I'm talking about.
Jang Mi and Baek Ho are geniuses.

181
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,300
Without Jang Mi's flawless planning
and bold execution,

182
00:09:26,370 --> 00:09:28,170
it would have been impossible.

183
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,070
The operation was perfect
because it saw right through...

184
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,840
Chae Hwa Young's endless greed.

185
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:36,680
If it wasn't for your mother,
it would've taken much longer.

186
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:41,850
She showed up at the perfect moment
and completely turned the tables.

187
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:46,120
My dear son-in-law Kang's legal advice
was a huge help too.

188
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,790
"Son-in-law Kang?"

189
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:52,230
- Mom.
- Isn't Baek Ho my son-in-law now?

190
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,600
Isn't that right, my dear son-in-law?

191
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:55,500
Of course.

192
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:58,570
Then this son-in-law
will pour his mother-in-law a drink.

193
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,000
I'd love that.

194
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:02,170
- Here's to my son-in-law Kang.
- Okay.

195
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,870
Thank you.

196
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,480
- All right, cheers.
- Cheers!

197
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:14,490
The Scientific Investigation Unit
is creating a composite sketch using AI?

198
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:18,290
Are they creating a sketch to predict...

199
00:10:18,290 --> 00:10:20,490
what our Eun Hye
would look like in her 50s?

200
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,730
Yes, sir.

201
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:24,430
They say the sketch
will be over 90 percent accurate.

202
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:27,370
So they'll use a photo of Eun Hye
from when she went missing...

203
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:28,670
and combine it...

204
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:30,840
with the genetic features
of me and my wife, right?

205
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,800
We should have done this sooner.

206
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:35,410
It's not too late, sir.

207
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:42,180
We'll be able to find Eun Hye soon.

208
00:10:55,130 --> 00:10:56,630
I'm finished.

209
00:10:57,230 --> 00:10:58,530
My 30 million dollars.

210
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:00,770
My hard-earned money...

211
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,130
I'm ruined.

212
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,100
Completely finished.

213
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:10,880
The CEO Chae I know is someone...

214
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:13,740
who always shined her brightest
during a crisis.

215
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:17,820
I'm sure you'll find a way
out of this mess.

216
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,590
Are you mocking me?

217
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:24,960
A way out?

218
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,420
Did you say a way out?

219
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,230
Lee Kang Hyuk.

220
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:31,260
When that crazy Han Young Ja
stormed in here,

221
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,730
did you even try to stop her?

222
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,430
Are you actually having an affair
with Han Young Ja?

223
00:11:35,430 --> 00:11:36,970
Is that why you didn't stop her?

224
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:42,340
This is your fault.
This is all your fault. All of it.

225
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:46,110
Because you failed to deal
with the twins from the first place,

226
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:49,710
my 30 years of work
went down the drain overnight.

227
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:54,520
- Hwa Young.
- Don't say my name.

228
00:11:57,020 --> 00:12:00,560
No matter where I look,
there's no way out.

229
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,830
Oh Jang Mi and Kang Baek Ho
are closing in...

230
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:05,460
trying to throw me in jail.

231
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,970
That old geezer Chairman Ma
is sharpening his knife,

232
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,100
waiting to kick me out.

233
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,500
And if Jung Suk Hee...

234
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:13,500
is revealed to be Ma Eun Hye...

235
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,710
Just thinking about it is horrifying.

236
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,740
There'll be nothing left of me.

237
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:21,410
I'll just vanish without a trace.

238
00:12:26,820 --> 00:12:28,120
Kang Hyuk.

239
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:29,220
Yes, Hwa Young.

240
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,790
You were right.

241
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,590
- What?
- A way out.

242
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:38,830
Instead of cowering and just taking it,

243
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,830
I should turn the tables
and counterattack.

244
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:45,000
- Counterattack?
- Yes.

245
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:47,440
I'll just become
Chairman Ma's real daughter.

246
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:50,840
- I'll become Ma Eun Hye.
- What? Ma Eun Hye?

247
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:52,280
Yes.

248
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:54,250
I'm telling you I'm going
to become Ma Eun Hye.

249
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:56,810
Chairman Ma's biological daughter,
Ma Eun Hye.

250
00:12:57,350 --> 00:13:01,550
Not Jung Suk Hee.
I'm going to become Ma Eun Hye.

251
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,260
The biggest variable...

252
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:09,630
is not knowing the exact size
of Chae Hwa Young's slush fund.

253
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:13,030
There's no way the 30 million dollars
that Jang Mi took was all she has.

254
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,730
Chae Hwa Young
just lost 30 million dollars,

255
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,800
which is everything to her,

256
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:18,270
so she'll be scrambling
to make up for that loss somehow.

257
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:22,210
From now on,
we need to watch her every move.

258
00:13:22,210 --> 00:13:25,510
I'll stop by the Chairman's house often...

259
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:29,680
- and get a feel for the situation.
- I'll try to sweet-talk Yeom San Wol.

260
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:31,450
She's the one who sided
with Chae Hwa Young...

261
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:33,420
and helped kidnap my mother.

262
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,820
If I put the right pressure on her,
she might spill everything.

263
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:40,190
But Jang Mi,
shouldn't we tell the Chairman now...

264
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:43,060
that Chae Hwa Young lost
the 30 million dollars?

265
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:45,300
Wouldn't that be the best way
to get her under our thumb?

266
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:49,370
Actually, Baek Ho and I are already
preparing a report for the Chairman.

267
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:51,240
What?

268
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,340
Chairman Ma
ordered an AI composite sketch?

269
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:56,510
The Scientific Investigation Unit
of the police...

270
00:13:56,510 --> 00:14:00,410
is creating a composite sketch to predict
what Ma Eun Hye looks like now in her 50s?

271
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:02,950
No way, Kang Hyuk.

272
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:05,820
Find someone inside the police right now.

273
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,320
I don't care how much it costs.

274
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:10,520
Stop them from making
the composite sketch, no matter what.

275
00:14:10,590 --> 00:14:15,430
I don't care about the cost.
Stop the composite sketch, no matter what.

276
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:17,530
If that composite sketch gets out,

277
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,830
Chairman Ma will recognize
Jung Suk Hee's face immediately.

278
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,170
- I'm sure they would.
- Kang Hyuk.

279
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:26,140
Just stopping them isn't enough.
Let's change the game entirely.

280
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:29,310
What? Change the game?

281
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:31,510
Change the face
in the composite sketch to mine.

282
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:34,310
The AI is just making a prediction anyway.

283
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:36,880
Just mix in some of my facial features...

284
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:40,050
and alter the composite sketch
to make it look like I'm Ma Eun Hye.

285
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:43,350
You want me to alter data
from the Scientific Investigation Unit?

286
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:47,260
That's too risky, and it's a huge job.

287
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:50,130
The police won't budge
for just any amount of money.

288
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:54,430
How many gold bars do we have?
Gold bars are untraceable and tax-free.

289
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:57,940
Find a cop who's desperate for cash
and drowning in debt,

290
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:01,140
- and bribe them with that.
- You want to use the gold bars?

291
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,210
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

292
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,180
Hello.

293
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:11,450
What?

294
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:14,020
The police station's center
for missing children?

295
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:18,560
Okay, I understand.
We'll go and re-register today.

296
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:19,790
Okay.

297
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:21,490
Mom.

298
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:24,360
Let's go register your DNA today.

299
00:15:24,430 --> 00:15:26,300
- Now?
- Yes.

300
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,000
While you were pretending
to be Chairman Ali,

301
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,500
you went through so much.

302
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:33,270
How about you focus on finding
your parents now?

303
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:38,140
But I doubt they're still alive
after all this time.

304
00:15:54,590 --> 00:15:56,430
Proceed as planned.

305
00:15:56,930 --> 00:16:00,000
And make sure they don't suspect a thing.

306
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:05,370
(Missing Children Campaign)

307
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:06,870
Hello.

308
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:08,140
You must be Jung Suk Hee.

309
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:12,580
I'm Detective Choi who called.
Please have a seat.

310
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:16,350
Yes. I'd forgotten all about it,
so thank you for calling.

311
00:16:16,410 --> 00:16:18,350
It's all part of the job.

312
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:22,990
Then, to get a sample,
I'm going to do a mouth swab.

313
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:24,420
Okay.

314
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:27,960
- It'll be okay.
- Open your mouth, please.

315
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:29,030
Okay.

316
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:33,000
Okay, all done. Just a moment.

317
00:16:36,970 --> 00:16:40,870
(Oral Mucosa Cells)

318
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:44,270
(Buccal Epithelial Cells)

319
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:53,250
(Buccal Epithelial Cells)

320
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,150
(Registration Confirmation)

321
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:57,820
(Certificate of DNA Sample Collection)

322
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:02,660
Okay, we're all finished.
You can take this confirmation with you.

323
00:17:03,060 --> 00:17:05,430
Why are you putting that one aside?

324
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,730
(Buccal Epithelial Cells)

325
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:13,370
Well, it looks like this kit is defective.

326
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,710
It has to be discarded
if it gets contaminated.

327
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:20,280
And this was just a backup,
so this one is enough.

328
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:24,010
So please don't worry.
Just take the confirmation with you.

329
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,750
- Okay.
- Here.

330
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:27,420
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

331
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,520
(Your Attention Brings Hope
to Missing Children and Their Families)

332
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:50,970
(Jung Suk Hee)

333
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:03,890
Did you swap the samples?

334
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:07,620
- Yes, I swapped them perfectly.
- Good.

335
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:12,460
This is the original photo
of CEO Chae as a child.

336
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,370
Enter it
into the AI composite sketch database...

337
00:18:15,370 --> 00:18:16,370
at the forensics lab.

338
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,070
But Manager Lee.

339
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,310
Where is what you promised me?

340
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:31,050
It's 99 percent pure.

341
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:32,680
It's worth over 300,000 dollars.

342
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,820
It can't be traced,

343
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:38,220
so cash it out
and pay off your gambling debts.

344
00:18:39,190 --> 00:18:40,790
But if you talk to anyone about this,

345
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,800
you're a dead man.

346
00:18:46,430 --> 00:18:47,430
Understood.

347
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:54,640
Are you feeling hot?

348
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:58,940
Why are you so shiny?
Is that sweat or what?

349
00:18:59,010 --> 00:19:00,240
Are you breaking out in a cold sweat?

350
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:06,720
Sir, the AI composite sketch
from the cyber investigation unit is here.

351
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:08,850
Let me see it.

352
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:16,590
You take it out.

353
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:21,470
This is Miss Eun Hye's
AI virtual composite sketch...

354
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:22,730
age-progressed to the present.

355
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:24,970
So this is what our Eun Hye
would look like...

356
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:26,170
if she were alive?

357
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,840
(AI Age-Progression
Composite Sketch Report)

358
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:33,440
This woman's face...

359
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:39,720
Father, I'm home.

360
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:42,650
You're both in the living room.

361
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:45,390
The woman in this photo...

362
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:49,860
- Doesn't she look just like Hwa Young?
- What's that supposed to mean?

363
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:53,100
Who is this woman
and why are you saying she looks like me?

364
00:19:55,670 --> 00:19:56,870
Well...

365
00:19:58,770 --> 00:19:59,840
Even the bridge of her nose...

366
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,340
She's a spitting image.

367
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:04,940
So you were looking at my picture.

368
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:07,980
What are you talking about?

369
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:10,380
Secretary Kim.

370
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:12,950
Come to my study.

371
00:20:18,490 --> 00:20:20,760
Why is everyone acting so strange
about my picture?

372
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:22,130
What is it?

373
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:27,160
- It's nothing.
- Yeom San Wol, didn't you hear me?

374
00:20:28,170 --> 00:20:31,970
No way. This is ridiculous.

375
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,070
No way...

376
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,870
Oh my goodness.

377
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:38,210
I must've seen it wrong.

378
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:41,810
I must be crazy. I'm seeing things.

379
00:20:45,350 --> 00:20:48,890
Everyone is going to freak out
when they find out I'm Ma Eun Hye.

380
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:52,690
This picture...

381
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,490
Are you sure this came from the police?

382
00:20:55,490 --> 00:20:58,630
Yes, sir. I received it directly
from the detective in charge...

383
00:20:58,930 --> 00:21:01,200
and brought it straight here
without opening it,

384
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:03,430
so there's no way
it could've been manipulated.

385
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:04,940
Then...

386
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:10,370
Why does Eun Hye's face
look exactly like Chae Hwa Young's?

387
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,610
This can't be a coincidence.

388
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,310
Sir.

389
00:21:15,150 --> 00:21:16,510
Wasn't there always a boy...

390
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:20,780
who followed Miss Eun Hye like a shadow?

391
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,290
So what?

392
00:21:22,290 --> 00:21:26,160
What if that boy
was Manager Lee Kang Hyuk?

393
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,260
Shut up.

394
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:30,330
There's no way Chae Hwa Young
is my flesh and blood.

395
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,860
She can't possibly be my daughter.

396
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:36,170
Absolutely not. Never.

397
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:37,800
Listen.

398
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:43,740
Don't trust the police.
I want you to look into it again yourself.

399
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:47,680
From top to bottom,
leave no stone unturned.

400
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,180
Investigate it all again.

401
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:51,310
It can't be true.

402
00:21:51,380 --> 00:21:54,150
Chae Hwa Young can't be my daughter.

403
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:58,960
You old geezer,
so you're that desperate to deny it?

404
00:21:59,490 --> 00:22:02,330
In that case, I'll have to show you...

405
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:06,500
some definitive proof
that you simply can't deny.

406
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:11,640
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

407
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:17,010
What is it, Mom?
I'm busy so make it quick.

408
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:20,310
- Something terrible has happened.
- What do you mean?

409
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,580
It's about
that AI-generated composite sketch...

410
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:24,350
to find
the Chairman's biological daughter.

411
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:27,480
Secretary Kim just brought it
from the police station.

412
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:30,320
What about
the AI-generated composite sketch?

413
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:33,920
- The Chairman's daughter is Chae...
- What are you doing now?

414
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:35,990
Oh my...

415
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:36,990
Honey.

416
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,830
Who were you on the phone with...

417
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,270
going on about some composite sketch?

418
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:45,200
Well...

419
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:49,340
That picture is computer-generated.

420
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:51,910
And you're talking about
how it's CEO Chae or whatever...

421
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:53,440
Stop spouting nonsense.

422
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:56,180
Besides, don't you know
CEO Chae has parents?

423
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:58,880
She's not an orphan.
What are you talking about?

424
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,420
You don't know what you're talking about.

425
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:06,160
That's right.

426
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:10,060
I heard she has parents too.

427
00:23:11,660 --> 00:23:14,360
That's right. It's impossible.
How could it be her?

428
00:23:15,370 --> 00:23:19,070
No, that can't be right.

429
00:23:21,670 --> 00:23:23,670
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

430
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:27,910
What is it, Lawyer Kang?

431
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:32,480
I'm not here on business.
This is personal.

432
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:36,650
I'm planning a formal family meeting
with Jang Mi soon.

433
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:39,920
And if you try to ruin it like last time,
I won't let it slide.

434
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,990
Oh Jang Mi is dead.

435
00:23:43,060 --> 00:23:44,690
How can you have a family meeting
with a dead person?

436
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,830
If you're just going to spout nonsense,
get out.

437
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,070
I'm not in the mood for games.

438
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:56,210
I'll come back later.

439
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:57,870
Manager Lee.

440
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:00,610
Wait.

441
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:07,980
Does CEO Chae Hwa Young
happen to have a golden toad?

442
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:09,690
A golden toad?

443
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:13,720
A while back,

444
00:24:13,820 --> 00:24:17,390
when CEO Chae said she was pregnant
with a son,

445
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:20,060
I sent her one as a gift back then.

446
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,230
Chairman Ma said...

447
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:25,740
when CEO Chae was pregnant with her son,

448
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:28,170
he sent her a golden toad as a gift.

449
00:24:28,870 --> 00:24:31,840
He said it's engraved
with his family's unique crest.

450
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:35,750
Does she still have it?

451
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:52,500
(Chang, Sil)

452
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,970
Who gave you permission to come in here?

453
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:01,500
Get out right now.

454
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:03,370
Get out.

455
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:08,680
- Dad.
- What? "Dad?"

456
00:25:10,950 --> 00:25:13,720
What is this nonsense you're spouting?

457
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:27,600
(Chang, Sil)

458
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,830
How come...

459
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,770
Why do you have this?

460
00:25:32,870 --> 00:25:36,940
When that fake daughter showed up
and caused a scene,

461
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,980
you said something about a necklace.

462
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:43,050
Ever since I was abandoned
in front of the orphanage,

463
00:25:43,510 --> 00:25:47,480
I've had this half-necklace
that was tucked inside my baby clothes.

464
00:25:47,950 --> 00:25:50,620
I always thought the design was unusual,

465
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:52,920
but on the off chance,

466
00:25:52,990 --> 00:25:56,690
and out of curiosity,
I just tried putting them together.

467
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,930
I can't be the daughter...

468
00:25:57,930 --> 00:26:02,170
you've desperately been searching
for your whole life, can I?

469
00:26:02,230 --> 00:26:06,500
Right? It can't be. This is ridiculous.

470
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:11,910
How could a nameless orphan like me
be your real daughter?

471
00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:15,050
This is Miss Eun Hye's
AI virtual composite sketch...

472
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:16,280
age-progressed to the present.

473
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:20,180
What if that boy
was Manager Lee Kang Hyuk?

474
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:23,590
Then...

475
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:25,560
Are you...

476
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:28,460
Are you really...

477
00:26:29,690 --> 00:26:32,230
my daughter Eun Hye?

478
00:26:32,630 --> 00:26:33,660
Father...

479
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,270
No...

480
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,270
Dad...

481
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,880
Aren't you going to tell me
what's going on?

482
00:26:50,310 --> 00:26:53,250
- What is it?
- I'm not sure myself.

483
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:55,920
She said something about an AI photo
and then hung up.

484
00:26:56,150 --> 00:26:57,420
An AI photo?

485
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,860
What's the difference between an AI photo
and a real photo?

486
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:01,690
I think that's what she was about to ask.

487
00:27:02,430 --> 00:27:03,490
What?

488
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:05,860
Did my mom get into trouble again?

489
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:08,130
All right.

490
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:17,370
She definitely said something about
the Chairman's real daughter.

491
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:23,110
(Client B)

492
00:27:29,950 --> 00:27:32,990
(Client B)

493
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:04,720
(Client B)

494
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:08,530
The sample has been collected.

495
00:28:08,590 --> 00:28:12,600
I'll take it to the DNA lab right away
and request a VVIP rush.

496
00:28:12,660 --> 00:28:13,860
Wait a minute.

497
00:28:45,660 --> 00:28:47,730
(The First Man)

498
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:50,230
Choi Ha Joon? Born in 1993?

499
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:52,970
A young punk like him
is the majority shareholder?

500
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:56,840
Why does Kang Baek Ho
have that golden toad?

501
00:28:56,910 --> 00:28:58,170
Lee Kang Hyuk.

502
00:28:58,170 --> 00:28:59,780
What did he go there to find?

503
00:29:00,110 --> 00:29:03,150
The probability of paternity
between subjects A and B...

504
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:06,020
is over 99.999 percent,

505
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:10,320
confirming
a biological parent-child relationship.

506
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:11,690
Dad.

507
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,520
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
